Former ANC member of parliament Zola Skweyiya has died. Details about the cause of Skweyiya’s death are still not known but his family has confirmed his passing. He was 75 years old. Skweyiya was chosen by late former President Nelson Mandela as the Minister of Public Service and Administration during the country’s first ever cabinet in the new dispensation between 1994 and 1999 and as a Minister of Social Development from 1999 to 2009. In September 2009 after he announced his retirement from parliament, he was appointed as South Africa’s high commissioner to the United Kingdom and Northern Ireland. More to follow. -TNA Reporter   